rComments: Basically do the reading, work on the assignments and go to all classes. her lectures are very important. i took 3 courses with her and made an A on all. i am not native by the way. even natives who thought they were perfect could not get an A because they thought it was easy getting an A.i will recommend this course for non natives it is so good.

Having no connection to the Arab world I was a bit hesitant my first day of class. Throughout the year the prof was nothing but helpful. Whenever I felt overwhelmed (which was more than once) she was there to offer guidance and encouragement. I now have a great foundation of Arabic and I am glad that I took the course, overall it was a good year.
